SCENE 2 (1125-1189). The two old gentlemen come out of the house in conversation. Callicles has given an account of his stewardship, and Charmides has approved of all that he has done. Lysiteles listens to what they say, then v, 1 150 presents himself to them. Lesbonicus is pardoned, and all is arranged.
